story.title: Double - Episode 4
story.storyDescription: When Kate meets a stranger who looks EXACTLY like her boyfriend, she discovers that there’s more to this world—and her relationship—than meets the eye.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: EJ Hendricks is a writer with a passion for new media. She resides in New York City with her cat.

messages.text: I’m no artist…but the pentagram’s ready
If you can lure him this way, it should
I’m sending you my location now…
That fox noise is starting up again…
Except now it sounds like it’s shouting my name
It sounds like it’s saying “KATE, KATE!”
Okay, I can’t take this anymore…I’m coming to find you.
I’m in a clearing now…maybe I didn’t have a good signal before
Why the hell did you leave it here anyway??!
I don’t want to touch it but I’m not leaving it in the middle of the woods…what if a random kid finds it?
I’ve never held a gun before
I feel like I’m going to trip and accidentally shoot someone’s head off
I was just walking down the path…and there were two of you
I didn’t know which one was you so I quickly hid behind an oak tree
If you see this, please give me a sign…anything…
He took my phone, but I got it back
Wait…I can still see Trevor out there
How do I know you’re really James??
I knocked him out for a second, but he’s strong
I need you to come back out here with the gun
Kate, you said it yourself -- he’s going to kill me!
James! There’s no way I’m firing a gun
When my mom died, it was the worst thing that happened to my family
I’m not doing that to someone else.
You just aim and pull the trigger
I can’t tell if he’s corporeal
How will I know who’s who??
I’m the one who isn’t lying on the ground
But what if he gets up really quickly and I get confused??
Shoot quickly and it won’t be a problem
I don’t know if I can do this, James…
Okay…I’m coming out from behind the tree
I ducked back behind the tree but I’m watching…
I can see both of you
Omigosh, he really looks just like you
I can’t shoot if you’re moving…I might hit you…
Shit! I can barely keep my hands still
I can’t do this, I can’t do this…
James would never do that. Ever.
You must have stolen James’s phone
I can feel it…you’re not James
And I have to do this
I’m so glad you were able to tell it wasn’t me who was texting you
When Trevor stole my phone I thought I’d be dead
I ran back toward the house
When the bullet hit him he just…disappeared
The gunshot must have detached his spirit from yours…
He wasn’t close to the pentagram, but maybe it still trapped him
Have I ever told you that I’m glad you’re into this stuff?
I never thought it would actually come in handy
I’m still shaking so hard that I might puke
Are you back at your house?
